doc.after: In Northern Ireland Northern Ireland Railways NIR both owns the infrastructure and operates passenger rail services The Northern Ireland rail network is one of the few networks in Europe that carry no freight It is publicly owned NIR was united in 1996 with Northern Ireland s two publicly owned bus operators Ulsterbus and Metro formally Citybus under the brand Translink
